{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17594315","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17594315"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:45:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:45:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15299"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15299","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15299"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.46,0.07,0.39,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7990"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66613"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7990","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7990"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15299"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52066"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"29"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"8755"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19427"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19429"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21395"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66613","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66613"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old woman presents for investigation of right upper quadrant discomfort. Imaging reveals a 4 cm well-circumscribed liver mass. Microscopic examination shows sheets of hepatocytes without portal tracts, containing prominent sinusoidal vessels and scattered inflammatory cells. The cells contain glycogen and lipid droplets, with minimal nuclear atypia.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Cholangiocarcinoma","Hepatic adenoma","Hepatic haemangioma","Hepatocellular carcinoma","Primary hepatic lymphoma"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe features described are classic for \u003Cstrong\u003Ehepatic adenoma\u003C/strong\u003E. These benign tumours typically occur in women of reproductive age taking oral contraceptives. The histological features include sheets of hepatocytes without portal tracts or bile ducts, and prominent sinusoidal vessels.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatocellular carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E typically shows more nuclear atypia, trabecular growth pattern, and vascular invasion. \u003Cstrong\u003EPrimary hepatic lymphoma\u003C/strong\u003E shows sheets of lymphoid cells rather than hepatocytes. \u003Cstrong\u003EHepatic haemangioma\u003C/strong\u003E consists of dilated vascular channels lined by endothelial cells. \u003Cstrong\u003ECholangiocarcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E shows malignant glandular structures derived from bile duct epithelium.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Hepatic adenomas are benign liver tumours composed of hepatocytes, typically occurring in women taking oral contraceptives.","Hepatic adenomas are well-circumscribed, soft, tan-coloured lesions that can undergo haemorrhage or malignant transformation.","Key distinguishing features of hepatic adenomas include lack of portal tracts and bile ducts, presence of lipid-containing hepatocytes, and prominent vessels."],"references":["Torbenson M, Washington K. Pathology of liver disease: advances in the last 50 years. Hum Pathol. 2020 Jan;95:78-98. doi: 10.1016/j.humpath.2019.08.023. Epub 2019 Sep 4. PMID: 31493428","Chan WK, Chuah KH, Rajaram RB, Lim LL, Ratnasingam J, Vethakkan SR. Metabolic Dysfunction-Associated Steatotic Liver Disease (MASLD): A State-of-the-Art Review. J Obes Metab Syndr. 2023 Sep 30;32(3):197-213. doi: 10.7570/jomes23052. Epub 2023 Sep 13. PMID: 37700494; PMCID: PMC10583766","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Gasmi B, Kleiner DE. Liver Histology: Diagnostic and Prognostic Features. Clin Liver Dis. 2020 Feb;24(1):61-74. doi: 10.1016/j.cld.2019.09.004. Epub 2019 Oct 31. PMID: 31753251; PMCID: PMC6986808"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52066"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15299"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52066","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52066"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-01T15:37:39+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-01T15:38:04+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7990"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66613"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"29","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/29"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2c","name":"Pathology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"4"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","lin